partial_mortality.Rmd

Ross Cunning

5/23/2018

Import data

# Import tidy tagged coral data (does not include partial mortality)
load("../data/tagged_corals.RData")

# Import 2016 partial mortality data
ia <- read_csv("../data/DEP_responsive_records_May_2017/permanent_sites_impact_assessment_corals_2016_CSI_QAQC.csv", skip=1) %>%
  select("Date", "Site", "Transect", "Tagged coral (Y/N)", "Coral ID", "Species", "Visual Estimate % Mortality") %>%
  filter(`Tagged coral (Y/N)` == "Y") %>%
  rename("pct.mort" = "Visual Estimate % Mortality") %>%
  mutate(coral = interaction(Site, Transect, `Coral ID`),
         Date = as.Date(Date, format = "%m/%d/%y")) %>%
  select("Date", "coral", "Species", "pct.mort") %>%
  filter(grepl("^R", coral)) %>%
  mutate(pct.mort = as.numeric(pct.mort)) %>%
  distinct()  # remove duplicated rows


# Merge percent mortality with rest of data
pmor <- left_join(ia, alldata, by=c("Date", "coral", "Species")) %>%
  select(Date, reef, dir, Site, Channel, Transect, Coral.ID, Species, pct.mort, coral)
pmor <- pmor[!is.na(pmor$Channel),]  # A couple of spp IDs didn't match (data entry error?), so other columns did not merge. omit these rows.

Visualize partial mortality at each site

# Analyze loss of tissue
ggplot(pmor, aes(x = Site, y = pct.mort)) + geom_violin() + geom_jitter()

Test differences in partial mortality between channelside and control sites

For each species

pmor.mod1 <- pmor %>%
  filter(reef == "R2", dir == "N") %>%
  glm(pct.mort/100 ~ Channel * Species, data = ., family = "quasibinomial")

# Get lsmeans
pmor.lsm1 <- lsmeans(pmor.mod1, specs = c("Channel", "Species"), type = "response")

# Pairwise comparisons (channelside vs. control) for each species
rbind(pairs(pmor.lsm1, by = "Species"), adjust = "none")

Siderastrea siderea has significantly higher partial mortality at channelside sites (53.6%) compared to control sites (8.3%) on the northern middle reef.

For susceptible vs. non-susceptible corals

# WP disease-susceptible species
sus.spp <- c("CNAT", "DSTO", "DLAB", "EFAS", "MMEA", "MCAV", "ODIF", "DCLI", "DSTR", "SBOU")

# Add grouping factor for susceptible vs. non-susceptible species
pmor <- mutate(pmor, sus = factor(ifelse(Species %in% sus.spp, "sus", "nonsus")))

# Fit model
pmor.mod2 <- pmor %>%
  filter(reef == "R2", dir == "N") %>%
  glm(pct.mort/100 ~ Channel * sus, data = ., family = "quasibinomial")

# Get lsmeans
pmor.lsm2 <- lsmeans(pmor.mod2, specs = c("Channel", "sus"), type = "response")

# Pairwise comparisons (channelside vs. control) for each species
rbind(pairs(pmor.lsm2, by = "sus"), adjust = "none")
##  sus    contrast              odds.ratio        SE df z.ratio p.value
##  nonsus channelside - control   4.419137 2.9402796 NA   2.233  0.0255
##  sus    channelside - control   1.157862 0.4441115 NA   0.382  0.7024
## 
## Tests are performed on the log scale
# Plot lsmeans
plot(pmor.lsm2)

Non-susceptible corals had significantly higher partial mortality (48.3%) at channelside sites compared to control sites (17.5%).
